description: Borrowed from Middle French nautique, from Latin nauticus (“of or relating to sailors”), from Ancient Greek ναυτικός (nautikós).

adjectives.description: nautical (not generally comparable, comparative more nautical, superlative most nautical)

entries.meaning: Relating to or involving ships or shipping or navigation or seamen.
examples: I was mostly unfamiliar with the nautical terms used in the sailing documentary.
